subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis
. Medium-sized species (13.0– 
14.5 mm
). Body color gray brownish (
Fig. 3a
). Eyes black, without bands, with short, sparse ommatrichia. Frons divergent. Basal callus subovoid, with slight dorsal projection. Subcallus yellowish gray, without setae. Antenna brown. Maxillary palpus with yellowish pruiniscence, and short black and gray setae. Mesonotum dark brown, gray-pink laterally, with black and gray setae and two convergent stripes extending to near scutellum. Wing with clouds on the crossveins. Abdomen grayish brown, with short black setae dorsally and pale gray median triangles.

